Dar es Salaam. President Samia Suluhu Hassan has on Wednesday, July 20 appointed Camillus Wambura as Tanzania's Inspector General of Police. Prior to his appointment Wambura was the Director of Criminal Investigations (DCI). The new IGP replaces Simon Sirro who has been named Tanzania's ambassador to Zimbabwe. In the latest appointment the Commander in Chief of the armed forces also appointed Ramadhan Hamisi Kingai as the new Director of Criminal Investigations (DCI). In a statement by the directorate of Presidential Communication which was issued in the early hours of Wednesday, the latest appointees are set to be sworn-in today at State House Chamwino, Dodoma.